Hovi specifies that, in practice, the company must, for example, map out the job descriptions of its personnel on an individual level.
There will certainly be different levels of requirements depending on whether it is investment advice or selling products.
According to Hovi, another new feature is the requirement to work for a fixed period with someone more experienced if the skills or experience are not at a sufficient level.
That is, if the company hires a new employee who does not quite meet the specified criteria, the employee must work for a certain amount of time with the person who meets the criteria.
